# Architecture Shape LLM Guide

## Purpose

Use this command to validate configured file, symbol, argument, import alias, joined import, and line-count shape rules.

## When To Run

- After editing imports.
- After adding functions, methods, classes, or constructor arguments.
- Before finishing work that changed public shape or file structure.

## How To Read The Result

- Each violation names the rule, actual value, and configured limit.
- A limit of zero on boolean-style rules means the behavior is not allowed.
- Import alias findings mean joined imports or direct imports should be preferred.
- Line and count findings usually indicate the code wants a smaller unit.

## Examples

- If a function has too many arguments, introduce a clearer value object or split the workflow.
- If a class has too many methods, separate responsibilities by ownership rather than by convenience.
- If an import alias is flagged, import the named module or symbol directly.
- If joined imports are required, combine imports from the same source into one statement.

## Agent Tips

- Do not suppress shape findings with local exceptions.
- Make imports direct and joined when the configured rules require it.
- Split behavior only where it improves ownership or readability.
- Always rerun this command before final response.
